description: The rapid loss of species we are seeing today is between 1,000 and 10,000 times higher than the natural extinction rate. Researchers are concerned that factors including parasitic infections and climate change threaten the long term survival of moose. The removal of the Moose from this scientific illustration is meant to symbolize the possibility that this creature may one day only reside in photos like Lewis Carroll's Dodo.
